//! Socket layer — currently scoped to the `AF_ALG` (kernel crypto) family.
//!
//! # Where this fits
//!
//! The LTP `af_alg*` cases drive the kernel crypto API entirely through
//! sockets:
//!
//! ```text
//!   socket(AF_ALG, SOCK_SEQPACKET, 0)            -> algfd   [sys_socket]
//!   bind(algfd, sockaddr_alg{type,name})         -> select [sys_bind]
//!   setsockopt(algfd, SOL_ALG, ALG_SET_KEY, ...) -> key     [sys_setsockopt]
//!   accept(algfd)                                -> reqfd   [sys_accept]
//!   sendmsg(reqfd, data, cmsg)                   -> feed     (phase 2)
//!   read(reqfd)                                  -> digest   (phase 2)
//! ```
//!
//! # Phasing
//!
//! * **Phase 1 (this commit):** `socket`/`bind`/`setsockopt`/`accept` plus the
//!   algorithm-name registry in [`crypto`]. This is enough for `af_alg02`
//!   (CVE-2017-17806), whose pass path only `bind()`s names and relies on a
//!   nested `hmac(hmac(...))` being rejected with `ENOENT`.
//! * **Phase 2:** real digest computation on the request socket
//!   (`sendmsg`/`read`), wiring [`crypto::HashAlg`] to RustCrypto.
//! * **Phase 3:** `skcipher`/`aead` symmetric ciphers (IV/OP control messages).

